programme.title: Mortal Kombat
programme.desc: Hunted by the warrior Sub-Zero, MMA fighter Cole Young finds sanctuary at the temple of Lord Raiden. Training with experienced fighters and a rogue mercenary, Cole prepares to stand with Earths greatest champions to battle the enemies from Outworld.

programme.title: Bumblebee
programme.desc: On the run in the year 1987, Bumblebee the Autobot finds refuge in a junkyard in a small California beach town. When 17-year-old Charlie revives him, she quickly learns that this is no ordinary yellow Volkswagen.

programme.title: The Mummy
programme.desc: An ancient Egyptian princess is awakened from her crypt beneath the desert, bringing with her malevolence grown over millennia, and terrors that defy human comprehension.

programme.title: Blade: Trinity: Unrated
programme.desc: Blade (Wesley Snipes) and a pair of vampire slayers battle Dracula, the newly resurrected ancestor of the undead.

programme.title: The Conjuring
programme.desc: Paranormal investigators Lorraine (Vera Farmiga) and Ed (Patrick Wilson) Warren confront a powerful demonic entity when they try to help parents and children being terrorized in their secluded farmhouse.

programme.title: Ip Man 3
programme.desc: Martial-arts master Ip Man (Donnie Yen) takes on a crooked developer (Mike Tyson) and his gang of brutal thugs.

programme.title: Hollywood One on One
programme.desc: Hollywood celebrities give insight into their personal and professional lives, and open up about upcoming projects.

programme.title: The International
programme.desc: An Interpol agent (Clive Owen) and a New York prosecutor (Naomi Watts) join forces to shut down a powerful banks funding of terrorism.

programme.title: The Rundown
programme.desc: Before his retirement, a bounty hunter (The Rock) must locate his boss son (Seann William Scott), who is searching for a priceless artifact in the Amazon.

programme.title: Mortal Kombat: The Movie
programme.desc: Three unknowing martial artists are summoned to a mysterious island to compete in a tournament whose outcome will decide the fate of the world.

programme.title: King Richard
programme.desc: Armed with a clear vision and a brazen, 78-page plan, determined father and coach Richard Williams inspires his two daughters, Venus and Serena, to become tennis champions.

programme.title: Frantic
programme.desc: A U.S. doctor (Harrison Ford) follows a woman (Emmanuelle Seigner) on the fringe to find his kidnapped wife (Betty Buckley) in Paris.

programme.title: Oceans Eleven

programme.title: The Lodge
programme.desc: During a family retreat to a remote winter cabin, a man leaves his two children in the care of his new girlfriend, Grace. Isolated and alone, a blizzard traps them inside the lodge as terrifying events summon specters from Graces dark past.

programme.title: House of Wax
programme.desc: Friends (Elisha Cuthbert, Chad Michael Murray) become stranded in a town where murderous twins entomb their victims in wax.

programme.title: The Nun
programme.desc: Vatican officials send a priest and a novitiate to investigate the suicide of a young nun in Romania. They soon find themselves in a fight for their lives when they encounter a demonic force that takes the shape of a nun.

programme.title: The Convent
programme.desc: During the 17th century, a young woman is saved from execution by the timely intervention of a reverend mother. Shes led to a secluded priory, where she begins to experience terrifying visions.

programme.title: Burn
programme.desc: Melinda is a lonely and unstable gas-station attendant whos tired of being overshadowed by her more confident and outgoing co-worker. When a robber holds up the station at gunpoint, Melinda tries to make a connection with the desperate thief.

programme.title: The Foreigner

programme.title: Shazam!
programme.desc: Billy Batson is a streetwise 14-year-old who can magically transform into the adult superhero Shazam simply by shouting out one word. His newfound powers soon get put to the test when he squares off against the evil Dr. Thaddeus Sivana.

programme.title: Shazam! Fury of the Gods
programme.desc: When a vengeful trio of ancient gods arrives on Earth in search of the magic stolen from them long ago, Shazam and his allies get thrust into a battle for their superpowers, their lives, and the fate of the world.

programme.title: Justice League
programme.desc: Fueled by his restored faith in humanity and inspired by Supermans selfless act, Batman and his new ally Wonder Woman recruit Aquaman, Cyborg and the Flash to help them save the planet from a newly awakened enemy.

programme.title: Transformers
programme.desc: An ancient struggle between two Cybertronian races, the heroic Autobots and the evil Decepticons, comes to Earth, with a clue to the ultimate power held by a teenager.

programme.title: Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen
programme.desc: Sam Witwicky leaves the Autobots behind for a normal life. But when his mind is filled with cryptic symbols, the Decepticons target him and he is dragged back into the Transformers war.

programme.title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon
programme.desc: Sam Witwicky and his new girlfriend, Carly, join the fray when the evil Decepticons renew their longstanding war against the Autobots. The war appears to tip in favor of the Decepticons, leading to a climactic battle in Chicago.

programme.title: No Time to Die
programme.desc: Recruited to rescue a kidnapped scientist, globe-trotting spy James Bond finds himself hot on the trail of a mysterious villain whos armed with a dangerous new technology.

programme.title: Kipchoge: The Last Milestone
programme.desc: Kenyan long-distance runner Eliud Kipchoge tries to break one of the last milestones in sports history -- finishing a marathon in under two hours.

programme.title: Hollywood on Set
programme.sub-title: Captain Marvel; A Madea Family Funeral; Five Feet Apart
programme.desc: Features behind-the-scenes footage from movie sets and discussions with the cast and crew about the details of each film.

programme.title: Rita Moreno: Just a Girl Who Decided to Go for It
programme.desc: The remarkable life and 70-year career of singer, actress and dancer Rita Moreno.

programme.title: Grand-Daddy Day Care
programme.desc: A man has to figure out a way to make extra money when his father-in-law moves in.

programme.title: The Scorpion King: Book of Souls
programme.desc: Two fierce warriors search for the powerful Book of Souls to fight an evil warlord.

programme.title: Pokemon Detective Pikachu
programme.desc: Tim man joins forces with Detective Pikachu to unravel the mystery behind his fathers disappearance. Chasing clues through the streets of Ryme City, the duo soon discovers a plot that poses a threat to the Pokemon universe.

programme.title: Around the World in 80 Days
programme.desc: With help from his two sidekicks (Jackie Chan, Cecile de France), an eccentric inventor (Steve Coogan) bets he can circle the globe in less than three months.

programme.title: The Karate Kid Part III
programme.desc: Mr. Miyagi (Noriyuki "Pat" Morita) and his student (Ralph Macchio) open a bonsai-tree shop, then fight thugs sent by a millionaire toxic-waste dumper.

programme.title: The Creator
